{% layout "layouts/base.liquid" %}
{% block title %}Accessibility — Cubito UI Docs{% endblock %}

{% block content %}
<article class="flow">

  <header class="flow" style="padding-block-end: var(--space-l); border-block-end: var(--border-s) solid var(--color-neutral-200);">
    <nav aria-label="Breadcrumb" class="breadcrumb">
      <ol>
        <li><a href="/">Home</a></li>
        <li><a href="/utilities/">Utilities</a></li>
        <li aria-current="page">Accessibility</li>
      </ol>
    </nav>
    <h1>Accessibility</h1>
    <p class="text-m color-neutral-600">Skip-link and visually-hidden utilities that keep content reachable by screen readers without affecting visual layout.</p>
  </header>

  <section>
    <div class="flow" style="--flow-space: var(--space-s);">
      <h2 class="heading-l">Skip link</h2>
      <p>The <code>.skip-link</code> is the first focusable element on the page. It is clipped off-screen until it receives keyboard focus, at which point it snaps into view so keyboard users can jump straight to the main content and bypass the navigation.</p>
      <p>Place it as the very first child of <code>&lt;body&gt;</code>, before any navigation or header elements.</p>
    
      <div class="">
  <div style="position: relative; height: 4rem; overflow: hidden; background: var(--color-neutral-50); border-radius: var(--border-radius-m);">
    <a href="#main-content" class="skip-link">Skip to main content</a>
    <p style="padding: 1rem; font-size: var(--font-size-s); color: var(--color-neutral-500)">Tab into this area to see the skip link appear.</p>
  </div>
      </div>

      <details class="margin-y-s">
        <summary>Show code</summary>
        <pre class="padding-m"><code>&lt;div style=&quot;position: relative; height: 4rem; overflow: hidden; background: var(--color-neutral-50); border-radius: var(--border-radius-m);&quot;&gt;
    &lt;a href=&quot;#main-content&quot; class=&quot;skip-link&quot;&gt;Skip to main content&lt;/a&gt;
    &lt;p style=&quot;padding: 1rem; font-size: var(--font-size-s); color: var(--color-neutral-500)&quot;&gt;Tab into this area to see the skip link appear.&lt;/p&gt;
  &lt;/div&gt;</code></pre>
      </details>
  
    </div>
  </section>

  <section>
    <div class="flow" style="--flow-space: var(--space-s);">
      <h2 class="heading-l">Visually hidden</h2>
      <p>Both <code>.sr-only</code> and <code>.visually-hidden</code> hide content visually while keeping it accessible to screen readers and keyboard users. They use <code>clip-path: inset(50%)</code> rather than <code>display: none</code> or <code>visibility: hidden</code>, which would remove the element from the accessibility tree entirely.</p>
      <p>Use this to label icon-only buttons, supplement decorative text, or provide extra context to assistive technology users.</p>
    
      <div class="">
  <button type="button" aria-label="Open notifications">
    <svg aria-hidden="true" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 20 20" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5">
      <path d="M10 2a6 6 0 0 0-6 6v3l-1.5 2.5h15L16 11V8a6 6 0 0 0-6-6z"/>
      <path d="M8 16a2 2 0 0 0 4 0"/>
    </svg>
    <span class="sr-only">Notifications</span>
  </button>
      </div>

      <details class="margin-y-s">
        <summary>Show code</summary>
        <pre class="padding-m"><code>&lt;button type=&quot;button&quot; aria-label=&quot;Open notifications&quot;&gt;
    &lt;svg aria-hidden=&quot;true&quot; width=&quot;20&quot; height=&quot;20&quot; viewBox=&quot;0 0 20 20&quot; fill=&quot;none&quot; stroke=&quot;currentColor&quot; stroke-width=&quot;1.5&quot;&gt;
      &lt;path d=&quot;M10 2a6 6 0 0 0-6 6v3l-1.5 2.5h15L16 11V8a6 6 0 0 0-6-6z&quot;/&gt;
      &lt;path d=&quot;M8 16a2 2 0 0 0 4 0&quot;/&gt;
    &lt;/svg&gt;
    &lt;span class=&quot;sr-only&quot;&gt;Notifications&lt;/span&gt;
  &lt;/button&gt;</code></pre>
      </details>
  
    </div>
  </section>

  <section>
    <div class="flow" style="--flow-space: var(--space-s);">
      <h2 class="heading-l">Supplementary context</h2>
      <p>Screen reader text can augment visible content without visually cluttering the interface. In the example below, the visible text "Edit" gains a visually hidden suffix clarifying which item it refers to.</p>
    
      <div class="">
  <div class="flow" style="--flow-space: var(--space-xs)">
    <div style="display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: space-between; padding: var(--space-xs) var(--space-s); background: var(--color-neutral-50); border-radius: var(--border-radius-m)">
      <span>Annual report 2025.pdf</span>
      <a href="#">Edit<span class="sr-only"> Annual report 2025.pdf</span></a>
    </div>
    <div style="display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: space-between; padding: var(--space-xs) var(--space-s); background: var(--color-neutral-50); border-radius: var(--border-radius-m)">
      <span>Brand guidelines.pdf</span>
      <a href="#">Edit<span class="sr-only"> Brand guidelines.pdf</span></a>
    </div>
  </div>
      </div>

      <details class="margin-y-s">
        <summary>Show code</summary>
        <pre class="padding-m"><code>&lt;div class=&quot;flow&quot; style=&quot;--flow-space: var(--space-xs)&quot;&gt;
    &lt;div style=&quot;display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: space-between; padding: var(--space-xs) var(--space-s); background: var(--color-neutral-50); border-radius: var(--border-radius-m)&quot;&gt;
      &lt;span&gt;Annual report 2025.pdf&lt;/span&gt;
      &lt;a href=&quot;#&quot;&gt;Edit&lt;span class=&quot;sr-only&quot;&gt; Annual report 2025.pdf&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;div style=&quot;display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: space-between; padding: var(--space-xs) var(--space-s); background: var(--color-neutral-50); border-radius: var(--border-radius-m)&quot;&gt;
      &lt;span&gt;Brand guidelines.pdf&lt;/span&gt;
      &lt;a href=&quot;#&quot;&gt;Edit&lt;span class=&quot;sr-only&quot;&gt; Brand guidelines.pdf&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;
  &lt;/div&gt;</code></pre>
      </details>
  
    </div>
  </section>

  <div class="callout wide" data-variant="brand" role="note">
    <p>Reduced motion is handled at the token level. The <code>--motion-duration-*</code> tokens collapse to <code>0ms</code> when <code>prefers-reduced-motion: reduce</code> is active, so all transitions and animations in the system automatically become instant without any extra CSS.</p>
  </div>

</article>
{% endblock %}
